description:
Corn Program consist of 6 components/activities:
1. Production Support Services (PSS) - to ensure availability of quality seeds and planting materials that can be accessed by farmers, establishment of storage facilities of bufferstock to be used as storage facility of seeds to maintain quality and ensure its availability in times of calamities;
2. Market Development Services (MDS) - facilitation of market matching activities to encourage marketing tie-ups and contract growing arrangements in the farm clusters;
3. Extension Support, Education and Training Support Services (ESETS) - conduct of trainings and information dissemination that would empower farmers and extension workers; 
